Here is a sample 3-day cardio workout routine for weight loss:

* High-intensity interval training (HIIT): 30 seconds of burpees followed by 30 seconds of rest. Repeat for 15-20 minutes.
* Cool-down: 5-minute stretching

Day 2:
* Warm-up: 5-minute walk or jog
* Steady-state cardio: 30-45 minutes of jogging or cycling at moderate intensity.
* Cool-down: 5-minute stretching

Day 3:
* Warm-up: 5-minute walk or jog
* HIIT: 30 seconds of jump squats followed by 30 seconds of rest. Repeat for 15-20 minutes.
* Cool-down: 5-minute stretching

Remember to listen to your body and adjust the intensity and duration of your workouts based on your fitness level and comfort. Aim to do at least 150 minutes of moderate-intensity aerobic exercise per week to support weight loss.
